The paper deals with communication complexity, which is a topic in both information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of mutual information and the focus on modeling uncertainty suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the construction of a class of functions and non-product distribution suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms.
